result.name: Sushi Nyoi

reviews.text: nice place, good services, excellent ingridents and my favour sushi restaurant

Really good service. From front reception, server and chef. Average food. Nothing wow about it. But kind of unfair since the week before I had Two Michelin Star Sushi Yoshi. Reasonable price. Nice decor. A bit too comfy at the sushi table bar. Can watch your food being prepared. Our chef was more friendly than the others.

Great sushi and great service! The chef tailor made a menu for me as I'm allergic to certain types of seafood. I found them really accommodating and friendly! The atmosphere was relaxing and quiet unlike a lot of other local restaurants where you have to finish eating within a time limit. The staff were also very polite and welcoming and ensured we were enjoying our food. Really great omakase experience! Would recommend to anyone that enjoys exploring unique restaurants in hk !
Good quality. The price is very reasonable too. Good value.
The omakase was excellent. Wonderful selection of raw and cooked foods. Great location & environment.
